developing countries and--

00:50:08.335 --> 00:50:09.210
ADAM BRAUN: Oh, yeah.

00:50:09.210 --> 00:50:11.124
100%.

00:50:11.124 --> 00:50:12.540
AUDIENCE: Just
finish my question.

00:50:12.540 --> 00:50:16.200
And what exactly
are the challenges

00:50:16.200 --> 00:50:19.590
that are preventing it
from happening as of today?

00:50:19.590 --> 00:50:20.860
ADAM BRAUN: OK.

00:50:20.860 --> 00:50:23.160
So great question.

00:50:23.160 --> 00:50:25.320
One, when I talk about
that 10-year vision,

00:50:25.320 --> 00:50:28.189
when I say we'll be in dozens
of cities around the world,

00:50:28.189 --> 00:50:29.730
many of them should
be international.

00:50:29.730 --> 00:50:32.441
So 18% of our applicants
are international.

00:50:32.441 --> 00:50:34.190
You have to have a
visa to work in the US,

00:50:34.190 --> 00:50:36.510
because we need to recuperate
our investment in you

00:50:36.510 --> 00:50:38.760
through livable wages.

00:50:38.760 --> 00:50:41.490
And so we can't take those
students on currently.

00:50:41.490 --> 00:50:45.270
But we've had applicants from
dozens of other countries.

00:50:45.270 --> 00:50:47.614
I recently gave a talk
in Singapore about this.

00:50:47.614 --> 00:50:49.780
And the main question from
all these representatives

00:50:49.780 --> 00:50:52.950
of the different countries was
how soon can this come here?

00:50:52.950 --> 00:50:55.510
And so we certainly have
ambitions to scale globally.

00:50:55.510 --> 00:50:57.990
I think right now,
part of the challenge

00:50:57.990 --> 00:51:01.470
is the ability to deliver
live synchronous education

00:51:01.470 --> 00:51:03.480
over low bandwidth internet.

00:51:03.480 --> 00:51:07.560
But that's increasing
exponentially every single day.

00:51:07.560 --> 00:51:11.670
And so I actually spent
a full year in 2015--

00:51:11.670 --> 00:51:15.330
I was leading the largest
digital initiative

00:51:15.330 --> 00:51:18.231
called the global Education
Platform for the UN Special

00:51:18.231 --> 00:51:20.730
Envoy for Education, which is
Gordon Brown, the former Prime

00:51:20.730 --> 00:51:21.960
Minister of the UK.

00:51:21.960 --> 00:51:25.140
And in that year, what I
spent observing and seeing

00:51:25.140 --> 00:51:28.250
was this huge proliferation of
mobile across the developing

00:51:28.250 --> 00:51:28.750
world.

00:51:28.750 --> 00:51:30.900
And so what I would
see at scale is

00:51:30.900 --> 00:51:33.180
people being able to actually
have these experiences

00:51:33.180 --> 00:51:35.610
on mobile in the
types of environments

00:51:35.610 --> 00:51:39.169
where Pencils of Promise
has historically worked.

